      "acceptanceCriteria": "Benchmark problems (cantilever beam, Hertzian contact) reproduce analytical solutions within 0.5%.",
      "rationale": "Standard benchmark cases including a cantilever beam under end load and a Hertzian contact sphere-on-flat were solved and compared against closed-form solutions. Maximum deviation was 0.3%, confirming correct implementation of linear-elastic and contact formulations. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates < 2% change in all QoIs between medium and fine mesh densities.",
      "rationale": "A three-level mesh refinement study (coarse, medium, fine: 85k, 210k, 490k elements) was conducted on the non-cannulated construct. QoI changes between medium and fine meshes were 0.8% (stiffness), 1.1% (yield force), and 1.4% (force at 40 mm). All below the 2% threshold. The medium mesh was selected for production runs. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
