      "acceptanceCriteria": "Force and displacement residuals converge below solver default tolerances; energy balance checked.",
      "rationale": "All nonlinear load steps converged with force residuals below 1e-4 and displacement residuals below 1e-5. Energy balance confirmed within 0.1% for each simulation. No divergence or spurious hourglassing detected. Required Gradation 1 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts completed and documented.",
      "rationale": "A senior FEA engineer independent of the primary analyst reviewed the model setup, boundary condition definitions, contact pair assignments, and post-processing macros. All discrepancies identified during review were resolved prior to production runs. Review records are archived in the project document management system. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Linear-elastic isotropic material model for Ti-6Al-4V with bilinear plasticity is appropriate for the load regime; documented justification provided.",
      "rationale": "The pedicle screw and rod are modeled with a bilinear isotropic hardening plasticity formulation calibrated to Ti-6Al-4V ELI coupon data. The UHMWPE test block is represented as a rigid fixture consistent with ASTM F1717 fixturing practice. Geometric nonlinearity is enabled for large-displacement loading to 40 mm. Model form choices are documented and peer-reviewed. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometry sourced from traceable measurements; input uncertainty quantified via Monte Carlo sampling (n=500).",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus, yield strength, and hardening modulus for Ti-6Al-4V ELI were obtained from the Q2 2025 material property database (coupon testing campaign). Geometric dimensions were extracted from production-intent CAD files. Input uncertainty was propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (n=500 Latin hypercube draws), contributing ±3.2% uncertainty to stiffness predictions. Re-validation of inputs against the January 2026 model revision is planned for the next assessment cycle. Required Gradation 2 is considered satisfied based on available data."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N=11 constructs from production-representative lots; dimensional inspection confirms conformance to drawing tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Eleven non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs were assembled from production-representative hardware lots. Dimensional inspection of screw outer diameter, thread pitch, and rod diameter confirmed all specimens within drawing tolerances (±0.05 mm). Sample size supports statistical comparison per ASME V&V 40 Table 1. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple test conditions (e.g., varying rod diameter or screw spacing) evaluated to demonstrate model generalizability.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted under a single ASTM F1717 configuration (35 mm screw spacing, 5.5 mm rod diameter). No additional test conditions were evaluated in this validation campaign. This limits demonstration of model generalizability across the design space. The factor achieves Gradation 1 only; required Gradation 2 is not met. This known gap is documented and accepted given the supporting computational sensitivity analysis."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA model inputs (geometry, material properties, boundary conditions) are demonstrably equivalent to as-tested specimen conditions.",
      "rationale": "Screw and rod geometry in the FEA model was verified against dimensional inspection reports for the N=11 test specimens. Material property inputs were drawn from the same production-lot coupon tests used to characterize the test hardware. Boundary conditions replicate the ASTM F1717 fixture geometry as confirmed by fixture drawing review. Equivalency is documented in the model-test correlation report. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) satisfy both the < 10% percent difference criterion and E/uval < 1.96.",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: 4.2% difference, E/uval = 1.31. Yield force: 6.8% difference, E/uval = 1.54. Force at 40 mm: 5.5% difference, E/uval = 1.42. All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria simultaneously. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical failure modes and regulatory submission requirements.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the spine and is directly related to adjacent-segment disease risk. Yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are standard ASTM F1717 acceptance metrics cited in FDA guidance for spinal implant submissions. All three QoIs are clinically and regulatorily relevant. Required Gradation 2 is satisfied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
